Ranger Help for: circle
=======================

SYNTAX:      circle <target>
USAGE:       Wilderness
SLOT COST:   NA
BASE SP:     30
SKILL TYPE:  attack

SUMMARY:
This skill allows a Ranger to circle around an opponent, gaining a
positional advantage in combat. A successful circle grants +15 to dodge
and +20 to hit for a limited duration. The Ranger must be in combat
with the target. This skill works best in wilderness terrain where
there is room to maneuver.

While circling is active, the Ranger also works for position behind the
target. When the circling rhythm slips into the target's blind side,
Ranger melee damage gains a major bonus. The effect lasts longer for
more dexterous Rangers, but the positional advantage comes and goes as
the target turns to face the attack. At present, getting behind the target
grants a very large melee damage bonus while that position holds.
